  <aspecttable>DB-HV-1969</aspecttable>
  <name>Combined entry + distant signal</name>
  <reference>See <a href="http://www.sh1.org/eisenbahn/shhp.htm">sh1's page</a> or the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_railway_signalling#Home_signal.2Fdistant_signal_.28H.2FV.29">Wiki</a></reference>
  <description>Signal to use at the station entry, with distant signal head.
  Compared to a block signal it can also show "slow" because going through diverging switches may require a speed restriction.
  The top left light (usually never lit) is red and serves as a spare for the other red light.
  If main signal shows stop (Hp0) then distant signal is dark.</description>
  
